      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WALK ME DADDY (1) finds it hard to break through. Filled a minor placings again last time when third (17.47) at this track making it three placings in a row. Solid record here winning three races. Safe beginner who draws ideally on the inside. One of the contenders. MISS MOLIK (2) is mixing form and out of the placings last time but was a Grade 5 winner three starts ago and moves to Box 2 this time where she has performed well. Has good speed and aided by a low draw. Rates a winning chance on best. ALL ON WENDY (8) showed little early speed at her last couple, the latest finishing fourth (24.15) in a Grade 5 at this track. Safe beginner but wide box to overcome and will need some luck. Has ability and is one of the better chances. TODOROKI (5) was out of the frame here most recently but can atone.",
